@NODE "Introduction" "Introduction"

 @{FG SHINE}@{U}Introduction@{UU}:@{FG TEXT}

   FileSploin is a small proggie to split and join files. It has many nice
   features:
   @{B}*@{UB} Fontsensitive GUI.
   @{B}*@{UB} It uses very little memory.
   @{B}*@{UB} It's small.
   @{B}*@{UB} It's quite fast.
   @{B}*@{UB} It's very easy to use.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Disclaimer" "Disclaimer"

 @{FG SHINE}@{U}Disclaimer@{UU}:@{FG TEXT}

   You are using this program at your own risk. I'm NOT responsible for
   anything this program might do. (@{B}Although it shouldn't do any damage!@{UB})
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Copyright" "Copyright"

 @{FG SHINE}@{U}Copyright@{UU}:@{FG TEXT}

   FileSploin is ©Copyright Lorens Johansson 1998.
   This program is E-Mailware... If you use it then please send me an E-Mail
   so I can see how many people who uses this program... That's all I ask.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Requirements" "Requirements"

 @{FG SHINE}@{U}Requirements@{UU}:@{FG TEXT}

   · AmigaOS 2.0+ (Since ARexx was introduced in 2.0)
   · The following libraries in LIBS:
     rexxreqtools.library, rexxsupport.library, tritionrexx.library and
     rexxtricks.library.
   · It uses about 100k of memory.
   · SYS:System/Rexxmast MUST be running.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Install" "How to install"

 @{FG SHINE}@{U}How to install@{UU}:@{FG TEXT}

   Copy the program and the guide file to wherever you want.
   Copy the following libraries to LIBS:
   - rexxreqtools.library
   - rexxtricks.library
   - triton.library
   - tritonrexx.library
   That's it!
@ENDNODE

@NODE "HowTo" "How to use"

 @{FG SHINE}@{U}How to use@{UU}:@{FG TEXT}

   Please E-Mail me if you have any trouble with this program, and I'll
   do my best to help you!

   How to make the buttons in @{"DOpus4" LINK "DOpusbuttons"}.
   DOpus button usage:
   @{B}Split:@{UB} Mark the file you want to be splitted and press the button.
   @{B}Join:@{UB} Mark the last splitted file and press the button.
@{FG SHINE}____________________________________________________________________________@{FG TEXT}
ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
                                 S P L I T
@{FG SHINE}____________________________________________________________________________@{FG TEXT}
ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
    @{B}* Select the file that should be splitted.@{UB}
      This is where you select the file to split...
    @{B}* Size of the splitted files.@{UB}
      This is where you select the splitted file sizes.
    @{B}* Make BAT file.@{UB}
      If you check this option the program will make a BAT file for you.
      A BAT file is a file for use on PC, it will join the files without
      any use of an extern program...
@{FG SHINE}____________________________________________________________________________@{FG TEXT}
ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
                                  J O I N
@{FG SHINE}____________________________________________________________________________@{FG TEXT}
ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
    @{B}* Last splitted file.@{UB}
      Here you should select the last splitted file, eg if you have three
      files file.001, file.002 and file.003 then you should select the
      file.003 here.
    @{B}* Outputfile.@{UB}
      This is where you select the outputfile for, eg the file that the
      splitted files should be join up to.
@{FG SHINE}____________________________________________________________________________@{FG TEXT}
ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
