    @{B}* SPLITSIZE@{UB}
      The size which is used when you split files.
    @{B}* MAKEBAT@{UB}
      1 - If you want a bat file to be created when you split.
      0 - If you don't
    @{B}* PREDEFINED@{UB}
      Which of the things in the predefined cyclegadget that should be
      active:
      1 - No predefined.
      2 - MS-DOS DD (730000)
      3 - MS-DOS HD (1450500)
      4 - Amiga OFS DD (838000)
      5 - Amiga OFS HD (1676000)
      6 - Amiga FFS DD (880000)
      7 - Amiga FFS HD (1771000)
@ENDNODE

@NODE "DOpusbuttons" "How to make the buttons in DOpus 4"

 @{FG SHINE}@{U}How to make the buttons in DOpus 4@{UU}:@{FG TEXT}

   First you must start the config by pressing the 'C' buttons in the
   lower right corner. Then press 'Buttons'. Then you should press on an
   empty space to create a new button.

   @{FG SHINE}Split Button:@{FG TEXT}
    Write a suitable name in the name field, for example 'TU Split'.
    Press the 'New entry' button.
    Press the button to the left of the magnifying glass until it says
     AmigaDOS.
    Then you should write in the field to the right of the magnifying glass.
     Write: @{B}rx <path>FileSploin1.9.rexx SPLIT {f} {Rs Enter split size} @{FG SHINE}@@{FG TEXT} 1@{UB}
      You should put @{FG SHINE}0@{FG TEXT} where the @{FG SHINE}@@{FG TEXT} is if you don't want to make a batfile
      and @{FG SHINE}1@{FG TEXT} if you do want a bat file to be created.
    In the flags section you should press 'Output window'.
    Stack size : 4000
    Priority   : 0
    Close Delay: 0

   @{FG SHINE}Join Button:@{FG TEXT}
    Write a suitable name in the name field, for example 'TU Join'.
    Press the 'New entry' button.
    Press the button to the left of the magnifying glass until it says
     AmigaDOS.
    Then you should write in the field to the right of the magnifying glass.
     Write: @{B}rx <path>FileSploin1.9.rexx JOIN {f} {s}{Rs Outputfile} 1@{UB}
    In the flags section you should press 'Output window'.
    Stack size : 4000
    Priority   : 0
    Close Delay: 0
@ENDNODE

@NODE "History" "History"

 @{FG SHINE}@{U}History@{UU}:@{FG TEXT}

   @{" * " LINK "History-MBF"} History - MakeBATFile
   @{" * " LINK "History-Split"} History - Split
   @{" * " LINK "History-Join"} History - Join

   These three programs has been joined togheter to FileSploin.
   This program starts on version 1.4 because I added up the versions of
   the three programs it is made of and that makes it 1.4! :)

   @{B}1.4:@{UB} @{FG SHINE}(1998-09-30) (14101 bytes)@{FG TEXT}
   · It can now split files and make a bat file for it (not optional).

   @{B}1.5:@{UB} @{FG SHINE}(1998-09-30) (20268 bytes)@{FG TEXT}
   · You can choose if you want to create a bat file when you split a file.
   · You can join files.
   · Added some more error checking.
   · Added the AmigaGuide documentation.

   @{B}1.6:@{UB} @{FG SHINE}(1998-09-30) (21914 bytes)@{FG TEXT}
   · Added status. (Describes what FileSploin does when it works!)
   · Fixed some minor bugs in the errorchecking that didn't show one
     requester.

   @{B}1.7:@{UB} @{FG SHINE}(1998-10-01) (23512 bytes)@{FG TEXT}
   · It can take arguments now... so you can use it without the GUI. For
     example you can use it in DOpus. It has problem if you surround an
     argument with ""... :( I have a fix that isn't so pretty... If you
     surround somestuff with "" then you must add the argument 1.

   @{B}1.8:@{UB} @{FG SHINE}(1998-10-02) (24664 bytes)@{FG TEXT} First Aminet release.
   · Removed a bug in the make bat file routine.
   · It has some predefined splitsizes.

   @{B}1.9:@{UB} @{FG SHINE}(1998-10-06) (25075 bytes)@{FG TEXT} Second Aminet release.
   · Removed another bug in the make bat file routine.
   · And then I removed yet a bug in the make bat file routine, but it do
     really work 100% now... :)

@ENDNODE

@NODE "History-MBF" "History - MakeBATFile"

 @{FG SHINE}@{U}History - MakeBATFile@{UU}:@{FG TEXT}

   @{B}0.1:@{UB} @{FG SHINE}(1998-09-27) (3680 bytes)@{FG TEXT}
   · Writes a BAT file to RAM:temp.bat. (Not optional yet)
   · It puts togheter a file named FIL.ZIP that consist of 3 files.

   @{B}0.2:@{UB} @{FG SHINE}(1998-09-27) (3937 bytes)@{FG TEXT}
   · The user can change the name of the file (but it still saves the file
     RAM:temp.bat) and how many files it consists of. But the number of
     it consists of doesn't matter, YET!

   @{B}0.3:@{UB} @{FG SHINE}(1998-09-27) (5607 bytes)@{FG TEXT}
   · Number of files is working if it is less then 1000. (And that's
     perfect because it can only be 999 on the PC program so it's working
     now.
   · If the number of files is greater then 999 the program stops.
   · If the number of files is less then 2 the program stops.

   @{B}0.4:@{UB} @{FG SHINE}(1998-09-27) (7490 bytes)@{FG TEXT}
   · The program saves the file with the correct name in RAM: .
   · Included version string so you can use VersionWB on this arexxscript.
   · Added requesters for some things.

   @{B}0.5:@{UB} @{FG SHINE}(1998-09-27) (26253 bytes)@{FG TEXT}
   · You can choose where to save the file, with a file requester.
   · Added a GUI!

   @{B}0.6:@{UB} @{FG SHINE}(1998-09-28) (11930 bytes)@{FG TEXT}
   · You can use tooltypes.
   · Added an AmigaGuide documentation.
   · Added menus.
   · Added shadowed buttons when it's working.
   · Added Progress Bar.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "History-Split" "History - Split"

 @{FG SHINE}@{U}History - Split@{UU}:@{FG TEXT}

   @{B}0.1:@{UB} @{FG SHINE}(1998-09-29) (383 bytes)@{FG TEXT}
   · Nothing really works yet.

   @{B}0.2:@{UB} @{FG SHINE}(1998-09-29) (1856 bytes)@{FG TEXT}
   · It split the files but only in one smaller file... :)

   @{B}0.3:@{UB} @{FG SHINE}(1998-09-29) (2504 bytes)@{FG TEXT}
   · It splits the files OK now. The splitted files can only be 64k/file.
   · Max number of splitted files = 9.

   @{B}0.4:@{UB} @{FG SHINE}(1998-09-29) (2504 bytes)@{FG TEXT}
   · Max number of splitted files = 999.

   @{B}0.5:@{UB} @{FG SHINE}(1998-09-29) (2750 bytes)@{FG TEXT}
   · Takes two arguments inputfile and size.

   @{B}0.6:@{UB} @{FG SHINE}(1998-09-30) (3809 bytes)@{FG TEXT}
   · The splitted files can now be as big as you want them to be.

   @{B}0.7:@{UB} @{FG SHINE}(1998-09-30) (3857 bytes)@{FG TEXT}
   · It names the files after the inputfile and adds a three digit number.
   · Added an AmigaGuide documentation.
@ENDNODE

